---
description: How to write branch names
globs: "**/*"
alwaysApply: true
---

A branch name represent a brief description of the changes in the diff if given or a summary of all commit messages if given.

Branch names should contain no whitespace and instead use dashes to separate words.

Branch names should contain a maximum of 5 words.

Where applicable, the name of the package where the majority of the changes have been made should be used as a prefix, e.g. core/ or vscode/. If spread across multiple packages, use a term like 'refactor/', 'fix/' or similar to indicate the type of changes.
